  "texts": [
    "The confirmed transaction data are kept on a secure distributed ledger.The ledger is a chained data structure.",
    "The data are encrypted and added to the chain in blocks.",
    "Unlike the traditional chain structure, each block contains the value of the previous block.",
    "In this way, a logical connection is formed between the blocks, and change or deletion of the blocks is prevented and thus strengthening the ledger against various attacks.",
    "As a global database, the ledger is accessible to everyone."
  ],
